==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uproar
<hw>Up"roar</hw> <pr>(⟦ucr⟧p"r⟦omac⟧r`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D.
<ets>oproer</ets>; akin to G. <ets>aufruhr</ets>, Dan.
<ets>opr⟦oum⟧r</ets>, Sw. <ets>uppror</ets>; D. <ets>op</ets> up +
<ets>roeren</ets> to stir; akin to AS. <ets>hr⟦emac⟧ran</ets> to stir,
<ets>hr⟦omac⟧r</ets> stirring, active, G. <ets>r⟦uum⟧hren</ets> to stir,
OHG. <ets>ruoren</ets>, Icel. <ets>hr⟦ae⟧ra</ets>, Dan.
<ets>r⟦oum⟧re</ets>, Sw. <ets>r⟦oum⟧ra</ets>. Cf.
<er>Rearmouse</er>.]</ety> <note>[In verse, sometimes accented on the
second syllable.]</note> <def>Great tumult; violent disturbance and
noise; noisy confusion; bustle and clamor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But the Jews which believed not, . . . set all the city on an
<qex>uproar</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Acts xvii. 5.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uproar</ent>⟦br⟧

